.TH LS 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ls \- list directory contents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ls
.RI [ OPTION ]...
.RI [ FILE ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
List information about the FILEs (the current directory by default).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-a
Show all files, including those starting with . (hidden files).
.TP
.B \-l
Use a long listing format, showing permissions, size, and timestamps.
.TP
.B \-F
Append indicator characters to entries:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
* for executable files
.IP \(bu
/ for directories
.IP \(bu
@ for symbolic links
.IP \(bu
| for FIFOs
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B ls
List files in the current directory.
.TP
.B ls -la /bin
List all files in /bin with detailed information.
.TP
.B ls -F
List files with type indicators.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR openat (2),
.BR getdents (2),
.BR stat (2),
.BR tree (1)
